The @SenateGOP's #COVID19 relief package fails the millions of Americans who are relying on their government for support as our country continues to fight the pandemic.

@HouseDemocrats passed the Heroes Act 4 months ago.

@senatemajldr, do better. https://t.co/fA8aVehphX

It's telling when a company would rather suspend operations in California than follow state labor laws and treat drivers fairly.

@Lyft depends on drivers to make a profit, so drivers should be able to receive fair pay and benefits. It's that simple.

This is corporate greed 👇 https://t.co/3dfWeSI65o

Thanks for the nomination, @SpeakerPelosi!

This #Pride I'm proud of the work @VetAffairsDems has done to ensure that women, minority, &amp; LGBTQ+ veterans have access to the high-quality VA healthcare &amp; benefits they've earned.

@RepJudyChu, you're up for the #HousePrideChallenge! https://t.co/dXWF9T6NOB

On my way to the Capitol to vote for the #CoronavirusRelief package.

@HouseDemocrats improved this bill to support real small businesses, help hospitals and healthcare workers, and provide funds to implement a national testing strategy. 

Let's pass this bill #ForThePeople. https://t.co/UtWdcpv13z

Today is a devastating day for our democracy and our system of checks and balances.

@SenateGOP let Trump get away with his abuse of power. This Republican cover-up and contempt for our Constitution is not surprising.

This is Trump's Republican party.
